{{refimprove|date=March 2018}}
{{Infobox Islands |name = The Brando Resort on Teti'aroa | image_name = Tetiaroa from sky.JPG | image_caption = Aerial view of The Brando Resort | image_size = | map_image = Karta FP Societe isl.PNG | map_caption = | native_name = | native_name_link = Tahitian language | nickname = | location = [[Pacific Ocean]] | coordinates = {{Coord|17|0|S|149|33|W|type:isle|display=inline,title}} | archipelago = [[Society Islands]] | total_islands = | major_islands = | area_km2 = 6 | highest_mount = | elevation_m = | country = France | country_admin_divisions_title = [[Overseas collectivity]] | country_admin_divisions = | country_admin_divisions_title_2 = | country_admin_divisions_2 = | country_admin_divisions_title_1 = | country_admin_divisions_1 = | population = 80 | ethnic_groups = | additional_info = }} [[File:Tetiaroa.jpg|thumb|Teti'aroa]] [[File:Onetahi.jpg|thumb|Onetahi]] '''The Brando''' is a private resort located on the atoll of [[Tetiaroa]] in [[French Polynesia]]. The Brando serves as a regulated airstrip, research facility, eco-resort and spa on the Motu of Onetahi. The resort consists of 80 staff and facilities management personnel.<ref>"[https://www.linkedin.com/search/results/people/?facetCurrentCompany=%5B%2210274106%22%5D LinkedIn]", The Brando, LinkedIn, February 3, 2018</ref> The atoll's inside on which The Brando is located is on a 99-year lease contracted by [[Marlon Brando]].
==Travel== Traveling to The Brando can only be commercially done by air. Air Teti'aroa flies private planes between the island of [[Tahiti]] and Teti'aroa. The airline's departure is located in a private terminal at the [[Fa'a'ā International Airport]] in Tahiti.<ref>"[http://www.tahitiislandstravel.com/our-experiences/air-tetiaroa Air Tetiaroa]",Tahiti Travel Islands, February 3, 2018</ref> Air Tatiaroa rates to The Brando Resort on Tetiaroa fluctuate with the regular, high and festive seasons.<ref>"[https://www.paltino.com/the-brando/pricing/#airtetiaroa Air Tetiaroa Rates]",Paltino Air Teteiaroa, April 9, 2018</ref>
== History == Construction of The Brando Resort began in 2009 by Teti'aroa Pacific Beachcomber SC. The first phase of the building included repairing the airstrip runway for smoother plane landing and lengthening the tarmac to meet current aviation standards. Additionally, a reef dock was constructed to enable shipments from the ocean to the lagoon side of the reef.
In February 2014, it was announced that construction on The Brando Resort was officially completed. In July 2014, The Brando was officially open to the public.<ref>[http://howtospendit.ft.com/destinations/48103-marlon-brandos-private-island-escape-in-polynesia the Brando opening in July 2014]</ref> Eight of [[Marlon Brando]]’s eleven children were involved in the project along with the Brando Estate.<ref>[https://www.forbes.com/sites/guymartin/2015/01/06/an-island-named-desire-11000-per-night-bungalows-on-marlon-brandos-tahitian-hideaway/ The Brando, Forbes]</ref>
==Ecology== The buildings are made using materials that are of local or certified origin, renewable, or recycled. There is a deep seawater air-conditioning (SWAC) system to reduce energy demands. Renewable energy sources such as solar power (from [[PV panel]]s) and coconut oil ([[biofuel]]) are used. The [[Zinc–bromine_battery|zinc-bromine<ref>[https://www.energystorageexchange.org/projects/1038 Tetiaroa Brando Resort battery type]</ref> flow batteries]] (used for storing the power from the PV panels) are made from recyclable materials. The resort's vehicles are electric or human-powered.<ref>[https://thebrando.com/stewardship/ The Brando]</ref>
